JSX - JavaScript XML / JavaScript Extension Syntax

JSX is one of the core concepts of React.
It is imported as a Part of "react" pacakage that is being added in the project.
JSX is similar to HTML.
It Contains JavaScript code as well in the same place with the help of {}
Babel compiles JSX down to React.createElement() calls.
  const element = (
  <h1 className="greeting">
    Hello, world!
  </h1>
);

const element = React.createElement(
  'h1',
  {className: 'greeting'},
  'Hello, world!'
);
const element = {
  type: 'h1',
  props: {
    className: 'greeting',
    children: 'Hello, world!'
  }
};
